"Murder She Wrote" is the best thing that ever happened to TV!  The entire series 1 through 12 is spellbinding.  I have been a devoted fan of this series with Angela Lansbury all through the years.  Now, I am happy to say, I own the entire series on DVD and watch them over and over.  Whenever I want to relax with a good friend like Angela Lansbury I have the entire series to fall back on.  I never tire of any of them.  I have watched some of them as many as three times in one sitting.  They are great!

I would highly recommend the "Murder She Wrote" series to anyone who loves mystery stories.  Watch one and you are hooked for life!

This delightful TV series came out in the 1980s and can still be seen in reruns today.  The marvelous Angela Lansbury plays Jessica Fletcher, small town Mainer and mystery novelist, (who becomes a bit more sophisticated as the series continues).  Ms. Lansbury's performance never varies - it's always excellent - as she takes her warm and appealing character through solving one murder mystery after another.  Why buy the DVDs when you can watch the show in reruns on TV?  because you can tune in any time you want - and not have to watch a single commercial.  Highly recommend the entire series or any portion thereof.

I recommend this product to viewers who long for more elegance and less gore in their detective stories.  The plots are well constructed, the  decor is in good taste and Angela Lansbury is a pleasure to watch, even if sometimes her character (like other main characters in other series--- Miss Marple, Poirot, James Bond, etc) is introduced a bit artificially. But, once the plot is launched, it is all suspense and eminently enjoyable.

Wonderful stories of murder and a rather reluctant Jessica Fletcher/crime solver/writer, a series that celebrates one womens crime solving abilities when the police and other branches of the law fall short in their investagations. I Love it when her light bulb moments happen and always try to figure out who-done-it with her. I'm amazed somtimes at who the culprit turns out to be. I also get a lot of laughs, that balance out the drama well. Always there to help out a friend in need, set in many locations around the world. Wonderful in my eyes. Something I can watch without all the blood, gore and sexual mess of so many detective programs of today.
